snippet: Residents and officials are just beginning to assess the damage and determine the causes, even as fire crews continued struggling to get five of the blazes under control.
abstract: California residents are just beginning to assess damage and determine causes after 11 wildfires consume more 20,000 acres across San Diego County; fire crews continue to struggle to get five of the blazes under control.

byline.contributor: Jennifer Medina contributed reporting from Los Angeles, and Henry Fountain from New York.

lead_paragraph: Residents and officials are just beginning to assess the damage and determine the causes, even as fire crews continued struggling to get five of the blazes under control.

headline.main: California Wildfires Spread Across Hills, Leveling Homes
headline.print_headline: California Wildfires Spread Across Hills, Leveling Homes
